    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Linux is a widely used operating system that is known for its flexibility and versatility. One of the unique features of Linux is its file system hierarchy, which is organized into a many directories that serve specific purposes. Folder structure of Unix OS and all distributions of Linux is same. Each directory has its own set of files and subdirectories that are used to manage various aspects of the operating system and data folders.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
